VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR THANKSGIVING EVENTS 
A number of San Gabriel Valley churches and organizations are offering hot 
meals and bags of groceries to the needy during Thanksgiving week. 
Organizers said that donations and volunteers are needed. Following are 
descriptions of some of the events that are planned: 
* The Hunger Program of the Pomona Valley Council of Churches will give away 
holiday food items Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday; 1095 W. Grand Ave., 
Pomona; call (714) 622-7278 to volunteer for three-hour shifts. 
* The People Place of Claremont and Pomona need help distributing food baskets 
on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.; two locations: 135 W. 
1st St. in Claremont and 450 W. Holt Ave. in Pomona. 
* Bethany Community Church of Pomona needs volunteers to help serve a hot meal 
on Monday from 5 p.m. to 8 p.m.; 1750 W. Holt Ave., Pomona. 
* New Gethsemane Church of God and Christ will hold an early Thanksgiving meal 
on Tuesday; 177 W. Monterey Ave., Pomona; volunteers should arrive by 10 a.m. 
* The Salvation Army in Pomona needs volunteers to help assemble food baskets 
on Tuesday from 10 a.m. to noon, and 7 to 8:30 p.m.; located at 490 E. La Verne 
Ave. 
* The Salvation Army in Pasadena needs volunteers to help hand out Thanksgiving 
food baskets on Wednesday from 9 a.m. to noon; 960 E. Walnut St. 
* Union Station, a Pasadena homeless organization, with volunteers from All 
Saints Episcopal Church, will hold its annual Dinner-in-the-Park on 
Thanksgiving Day, complete with entertainment; Pasadena's Central Park, located 
at Fair Oaks and Del Mar avenues; volunteers needed from 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 
p.m. 
* Tom's No. 12 fast food restaurant will close its doors for business on 
Thanksgiving Day to serve a free turkey dinner to the poor; servers needed from 
11 a.m. to 6 p.m.; 282 E. Mission Blvd., Pomona. MARY ANN SWISSLER 
